<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98650678193986></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98650678193986><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98650678193986>RE: So Many pets</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98650678193986#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=1517><span id=Scholar>Elrique</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>17 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Apr 5th 5:39 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.29]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Magicians are the MASTERS of the Elements...  We are able to cast a pet from each of the following "Elements" for each spell level starting at level 4 to 49...  <br><br>Earth: Strong as all get out, takes a punishment and roots the mobs in place<br>Air: Not as strong, but agile as all get out, can stun the mobs with his stun spell<br>Fire: Weakest physically, but has a built in Flame Shield and casts a Fire DD as well<br>Water: Fast regen, and second strongest of the 4...  Has a Cold based attack, and immune to poisons<br><br>As you can see, each has a set of strengths, but they also have weaknesses...  <br><br>Earth: Gets hit ALOT.  Takes alot, too, but can take a while regening all those HP's back<br>Air: Lightweight on the damage side...  Can dish out a bit, but can't take much...<br>Fire: Fastest damage dealer of all the pets, but dies rather quickly, unless you keep a real good eye on him...<br>Water: Doesn't have the hit points Earth does, doesn't do the damage that Fire does, and hasn't got the ability to dodge the attacks that Air does...  Still, Water is Many Magii's favorite pet, and many will go with Water over the others in solo situations...<br><br>Now, post-50's the pets get some additional abilities, such as:<br><br>Earth:  Warrior, with Bash, Kick, tons of HP's and alot of damage output REAL quickly...<br>Air:  Monk, with Kicks, and other neat Monkly Melee skills<br>Fire: Wizard, casting alot of DD and other types of spells (Waste of mana and time even trying this one IMO)<br>Water: Rogue, with the Back Stab doing upwards of 165, he's great in a group where you have a prime tank taunting...<br><br>And, then the ultimate pet, the collection of all the types, merged into a single Awesome, Wreaking, totally killing Machine...<br><br>The Epic Pet is a collection of the best of the other pets, hitting in the high 60's, with casting of Root, DD's and has an inate Damage Shield, and has alot of HP's and is BIG!!!<br><br>HTH<br>&nbsp;<br>Elrique Melnebone<br>Elementalist of Blood and Honor<br>Master Vending Machine<br>Veeshan</td></tr>
