	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just as a side note, because I learned this the hard way today! :<br><br>When you hit level 20, keep a few lapis handy until you've got at least one full bubble of experience, even though your level 20 and above pets use malachite as the reagent.<br><br>I was in East Karana fighting spiders and wolves, and got stepped on by Broon when I wasn't looking. I ended up back at level 19 with pretty cruddy faction (not KOS, just apprehensive at best) everywhere between Erudin and Freeport. And I didn't know where the jewel vendor in Highpass was! or if I would somehow luck out and she'd be apprehensive to me (she was) or dubious. There seem to be two or three factions in Highpass, depending on who you're trying to deal with.<br><br>So make life a little easier on yourself and carry some lapis around until you're sure you don't need it any more. When you've got level 20 good and secured, convert that lapis into practice runes so you can get research skill up a bit.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
