	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have noticed that there have been a SWARM of newbies ever since I stopped actively playing EQ.<br><br>In any case, none of the are 'the best.' They are all better or worse than each other in certain situations.<br><br>The earth pet is good for soloing very big mobs. It will last the longest, and does a very good job with a damage shield on it. Plus it roots a lot which helps for if you want to nuke a lot. The downside of the earth pet is that its root spell will stop fleeing enemies, which in some cases is not a good thing. Why not? Becuase when an enemy is fleeing your pet can kill it until it dies and take no damage. If that same fleeing mob is rooted, then the mob will keep attacking your pet, and your pet will take longer to regen after the thing is dead. Also, when you are in a close fighting and the mob suddenly stops fleeing becuase it is rooted, and attacks your pet, your pet might die.<br><br>The water pet is your normal all-around pet. Good hp, good agility, good damage...but not the best in any categorie. Two additional benefits of the water pet is that it regnerates HP faster than other pets and that it is totally immune to poison. If you are fighting things that poison, or you don't know which pet would be best to use, try out the water pet.<br><br>The air pet is good for not only soloing low blue cons, but also for fighting casting mobs. The air pet has the most agility of all the pets, which means once you get to about level 20, you will see a noticible difference in how much it gets hit compared to the other pets. The air pet casts a stun spell, which in addition to interupping things that cast spells, the stun has a very high taunt factor, and will keep the monster off of you and on the air pet. Plus, the air pet casts invisibility on itself, which makes it good for when you want to wander around dungeons. The bad thing about the air is that it has low hp and that until about level 20, its high agility won't do much since the pets' defensive skills are not very high.<br><br>The fire pet is good for when you want to do a lot of damage or kill something very quickly. If you want to kill mulitple low blue mobs, then you can use the fire pet to kill them very quickly. The fire pets damage shield that is casts on itself is much better than the one you can cast, and is the main reason to why the fire pet dishes out so much damage. Besides the damage shield the fire pet also casts a fire based direct damage spell a lot, which adds additional damage. The fire pet has HORRID hitpoints, so don't use it against monsters that are bigger than you, it will die quickly. It is best used against low blues, because it won't die nearly as quickly and can dish out a lot of damage. Also, in a group setting the fire pet is a good damage dealer.<br><br>Also, an additional note, if you are soloing, make sure you do more damage than your pet(ie. take off 51% or a little more of the monster's hitpoints with your direct damage spells). If you don't outdamage your pet, it will get half the exp. for the kill. If you do outdamage your pet, you get full exp. for the kill.<br><br>Former Addict of Everquest.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
